**Bubble sort algorithm:**
```c
int arr[] = {5, 2, 8, 1, 9};
int n = sizeof(arr)/sizeof(arr[0]);

// Outer loop: n-1 passes
for(int i = 0; i < n-1; i++) {
    // Inner loop: compare adjacent elements
    for(int j = 0; j < n-i-1; j++) {
        if(arr[j] > arr[j+1]) {
            // Swap
            int temp = arr[j];
            arr[j] = arr[j+1];
            arr[j+1] = temp;
        }
    }
}
```

**Also works for chars:**
```c
char arr[] = {'A', 'G', 'B', 'K'};
if(arr[j] > arr[j+1]) { /* swap */ }
```

**Key points:**
- Outer loop: `n-1` passes
- Inner loop: `n-i-1` comparisons (shrinks each pass)
- Compare adjacent, swap if wrong order
- Largest element "bubbles" to end each pass

