**Exhaustiveness Checking** = Catch missing union cases

**Using `never`:**
```ts
function moveExhaustive(pet: Pet) {
  switch (pet.kind) {
    case "fish": pet.swim(); break;
    case "bird": pet.fly(); break;
    default:
      const _exhaustiveCheck: never = pet; // ‚ùå If Pet has new type
      throw new Error("Unknown pet!");
  }
}
```

**How it works:**
- If all union cases handled ‚Üí `pet` = `never` in default (OK)
- If new type added to union ‚Üí `pet` ‚â† `never` ‚Üí TypeScript error
**Catches** missing cases at compile time

